Class AbstractProcess

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AuditDetail, java.lang.Comparable<Reference>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractColumnProcess, BIProcess, DbtProcess, LineageProcess
    public abstract class AbstractProcess
extends Asset
    Representation of a process in Atlan, with its detailed information. This class is not intended for direct use, and is thus abstract.
    See Also:
    for table-level processes, for column-level processes

      • generateQualifiedName

        public static java.lang.String generateQualifiedName​(java.lang.String name,
                                                     java.lang.String connectionQualifiedName,
                                                     java.lang.String id,
                                                     java.util.List<Catalog> inputs,
                                                     java.util.List<Catalog> outputs,
                                                     LineageProcess parent)
        Generate a unique qualifiedName for a process.
        Parameters:
        name - of the process
        connectionQualifiedName - unique name of the specific instance of the software / system that ran the process
        id - (optional) unique ID of this process within the software / system that ran it (if not provided, it will be generated)
        inputs - sources of data the process reads from
        outputs - targets of data the process writes to
        parent - (optional) parent process in which this sub-process ran
        Returns:
        unique name for the process
